  "wikitext": "{{Navbutton/Separation}}\n{{Object Infobox\n|icon = Bone Shards.png\n|image = Bone Shards Dropped.png\n|stack = 20\n|spawnCode = \"boneshard\"\n|droppedBy ={{Pic24|Don't Starve icon}}: {{pic32|Skeleton}}&times;2 ({{pic24|Hammer}})<hr>\n{{Pic24|Reign of Giants icon}}: {{pic32|Hound Mound}}&times;2 {{pic32|Bones}}&times;1 {{pic32|Tumbleweed}}(0.1%&times;3) {{pic32|Catcoon}}<hr>\n{{Pic24|Shipwrecked icon}}: {{pic32|X Marks The Spot}}{{pic32|Spoiled Fish}}{{Pic32|Blue Whale Carcass}} {{Pic32|White Whale Carcass}}<br>[[Ocean]] ({{pic24|Trawl Net}})<hr>\n{{Pic24|Hamlet icon}}: {{pic32|Dung Pile}}(25%)\n}}\n{{Quotes\n|wilson = Bits of bone.\n|willow = I don't think they make good tinder.\n|wolfgang = Wolfgang crush into even smaller bones!\n|wendy = Choking hazard.\n|wx78 = PIECES OF STRUCTURAL SUPPORT SYSTEM\n|wickerbottom = Remnants of a life well lived.\n|woodie = I wish I knew how to make bread.\n|maxwell = Grind them bones.\n|wagstaff = Dense and sharp! Quite optimal for weapon crafting.\n|wigfrid = Bits öf my enemies.\n|webber = Boney bits.\n|walani = I don't think a cast will help now.\n|warly = I could make a hearty stock with these.\n|woodlegs = Bits o'bone.\n|wilba = IT DOTH POINTY PARTS\n|wormwood = Sharp. Ouch!\n|wheeler = Who knew bone shards would be so useful?\n|winona = Whew. These got crunched real good.\n|wortox = Fragmented, like my thoughts!\n|wurt = Piece of something dead.\n|walter = It's a bone!\n|wanda = Whatever these bones belonged to is lost to time.\n|choose = wortox\n}}\n'''Bone Shards''' are an [[item]] obtained by [[hammer]]ing [[Skeleton]]s. They are used to craft the [[Saddlehorn]].\n\n== [[File:Gift Icon.png|32px]] Downloadable Content ==\nIn the ''[[Don't Starve: Reign of Giants|Reign of Giants]]'' DLC, Bone Shards can also be obtained by hammering [[Bones]], destroying [[Tumbleweed]]s, attacking [[Hound Mound]]s, or as vomited gifts from friendly [[Catcoon]]s. They are used in several additional crafting recipes, including the [[Bucket-o-poop]], the [[Rain Hat]], the [[Rain Coat]] and the [[Eyebrella]].\n\nIn the ''[[Don't Starve: Shipwrecked|Shipwrecked]]'' DLC, Bone Shards can be obtained by digging up [[X Marks the Spot]] treasure chests and by [[Hammer]]ing [[Spoiled Fish]]. Using a [[Trawl Net]] in the [[Ocean#Shipwrecked|Deep Ocean]] also has a chance to yield Bone Shards. They are used in a variety of additional crafting recipes such as the [[Snakeskin Hat]], the [[Snakeskin Jacket]], the [[Captain Hat]] and the [[Pirate Hat]], and can also be used at the [[Volcano Altar of Snackrifice]] in [[Seasons/Dry|Dry Season]] to delay the next eruption by 4 day segments, or 1/4th of a day.\n\nIn the ''[[Don't Starve: Hamlet|Hamlet]]'' DLC, Bone Shards can be obtained by digging through [[Dung Pile]]s. [[Pugalisk]]s drop between 22-46 bone shards, between 42-55 [[Snake Bone]]s and between 1-4 Spoiled Fish which can be hammered into 2 bone shards each.\n\n== {{pic|32|Icon Tools}} Usage ==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Bone Shards\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Twigs\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Jet Feather\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Saddlehorn\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Bone Shards\n|item2 = Straw Hat\n|item3 = Moleworm\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Rain Hat\n|dlc = Reign of Giants\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Bone Shards\n|count1 = 4\n|item2 = Twigs\n|count2 = 15\n|item3 = Deerclops Eyeball\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Eyebrella\n|dlc = Reign of Giants\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Bone Shards\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Rope\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Tentacle Spots\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Rain Coat\n|dlc = Reign of Giants\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Bone Shards\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Manure\n|count2 = 3\n|item3 = Log\n|count3 = 4\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Bucket-o-poop\n|dlc = Reign of Giants\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Bone Shards\n|item2 = Straw Hat\n|item3 = Snakeskin\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Snakeskin Hat\n|dlc = Shipwrecked\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Bone Shards\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Vine\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Snakeskin\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Science Machine\n|result = Snakeskin Jacket\n|dlc = Shipwrecked\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Bone Shards\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Rope\n|item3 = Silk\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Science Machine\n|result = Pirate Hat\n|dlc = Shipwrecked\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Bone Shards\n|item2 = Seaweed\n|item3 = Straw Hat\n|tool = Science Machine\n|result = Captain Hat\n|dlc = Shipwrecked\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Bone Shards\n|count1 = 4\n|item2 = Dubloons\n|count2 = 10\n|item3 = Cloth\n|count3 = 3\n|result = Lucky Hat\n|dlc = Shipwrecked\n|character = Woodlegs\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Bone Shards\n|item2 = Nightmare Fuel\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Pugalisk Skull\n|tool = Shadow Manipulator\n|result = Pugalisk Wand\n|dlc = Hamlet\n}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Bone Shards\n|count1 = 4\n|item2 = Living Log\n|count2 = 2\n|result = Bramble Husk\n|dlc = Hamlet\n|character = Wormwood\n}}\n\n\n== {{Pic|32|Placeholder}} Trivia ==\n* Bone Shards were first introduced in the ''Reign of Giants'' DLC. In the ''[[Don't Starve/Version History|Quality of Life]]'' update, they were retroactively added to the base game.\n\n== {{pic32|Blueprint}} Gallery ==\n<gallery captionalign=\"center\" hideaddbutton=\"true\">\nA Little Rain Must Fall.jpg|Bone Shards as seen in the poster for ''[[Don't Starve/Version History#March 12, 2013 - A Little Rain Must Fall|A Little Rain Must Fall]]'' update.\n</gallery>\n{{Resources}}\n__NOTOC__\n[[Category:Resources]]\n[[Category:Non-Flammable]]\n[[Category:Mob Dropped Items]]"
